This paper focuses on concept-based query expansion and re-ranking schemes for web document retrieval, which is a core topic in information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper also mentions the use of ontology-based expansion methods, which falls under the category of knowledge representation and reasoning (cs.AI). The use of semantic proximity measures and statistical results from a web search engine also suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.LG) and database (cs.DB) techniques. Finally, the paper discusses the improvement of precision in web document retrieval, which is a common goal in computational linguistics (cs.CL).
